just finished running my 8th mile and it ended in the most refreshing way possible…

It’s so easy to forget the point of what life is all about when you’re constantly stuck behind a desk or living in the trauma and pain you refuse to address. 

Life is suppose to be filled with love and belly laughter. With runs on the beach that end with a jump in to the clearest of blue waters. It’s suppose to be about sharing beautiful moments with the ones who matter most to you. Life is about living in your truth and sharing that truth with others.

It’s not about material things or the perception others will have of what you’ve amassed but America and an individualistic society can make it easy to forget what it’s all about.
most jobs really aren’t that serious tho 😭

A towel could NEVER touch my face..instead I use Intrinsics Silken Wipes 🧖🏾‍♀️💦

Here’s how I work them into my routine:

Step 1: Cleanse with @oneskin.co face prep (dab excess water off with intrinsic wipes)

Step 3: Hydrating Mist, currently using @eadem.co Mami Wata

Step 4: Serums, currently using complexe iribiol by BR and Double Serum by @clarinsusa

Step 5: Moisturize with @truebotanicals Ginger Tumeric Hydraglow cream 

Step 6: SUNSCREEN @shiseido

Bonus step: lip care - my go to is butter mochi by Eadem but I’m giving @rhode and their peptide lip treatment a try!

100K 🥹🤍✨

I don’t even have the words — just so much gratitude. For all 100,000 of you. Thank you. 💕

I didn’t start out with a plan. I just shared what I loved. During my Master’s program, I posted YouTube videos about public health. Then the pandemic hit, and I shifted to Instagram and TikTok, diving into fashion and makeup — because it felt like the right thing at the time.

But something was missing: I hadn’t found my community. So I went back to what lit me up — talking about public health, biotech, and career. The moment I leaned into my real passions, everything changed. You found me, and I found myself again.

Since then, this page has grown into a reflection of who I truly am — someone who loves cooking with friends, traveling, working in biotech, and slathering on body oil like it’s a personality trait 😂

Here’s what I’ve learned: When you live and share authentically, the right people will find you. Your community will find you.

This platform has brought me opportunities I never imagined. But none of this would be possible without you — this incredible, supportive, smart, curious, beautiful community. And after God, I owe it all to YOU.

To show my appreciation, I’m doing a ⭐️100K GIVEAWAY⭐️ — actually, 3 of them! One for each area of content I share:

Career
Skincare
Lifestyle (Bridal Edition 💍)
Details coming in three separate posts — so stay tuned and make sure you’re following!

From the bottom of my heart: Thank you, I love you, and I can’t wait for what’s next 💫

A healthy equity package will be dependent on your financial needs because if you join a boot strapped start up and need a guarantee that your equity will pay out a certain value after X amount of years, that may not be a healthy option to meet your needs. You may be better served joining an established organization (e.g., Google or Amazon). It’s easier to predict the payout for contribution with established companies. 

If you’re more risk averse then picking a boot strapped start up could yield a healthy and high reward. It seriously depends on the product and the team which is why I take interviews so seriously. I need to assess if others at the company are as committed to the exit strategy.
